The saveState method of a ContentProvider supplied to the CommonNavigator, in particular, the Common Project Explorer, is never called.
I traced this to org.eclipse.ui.internal.navigator.extensions.NavigatorContentExtension.saveState(IMemento aMemento) which has no code whatsoever.

By simply replacing this empty method with:

	public void saveState(IMemento aMemento) {
		synchronized (this) {
			preserveMemento(contentProvider, aMemento);
			preserveMemento(labelProvider, aMemento);
		}
	}

	private void preserveMemento(IMementoAware target, IMemento aMemento)
	{
	if (target != null) {
		target.saveState(aMemento);
		}
	}

the saveState now works for me. For example, my EMF derived model contribution to the Common Project Explorer will now successfully save and restore its expanded state.

