Who is adding the bidi control characters in the text ?

The quick fix for rule 'Avoid using if/else statements for short conditions' can result in replacement code that is not equivalent to the original code. 

For example, the following code:

if (newIsAbstract)
    eFlags |= IS_ABSTRACT_EFLAG;
else
    eFlags &= ~IS_ABSTRACT_EFLAG;

is replaced with this:

eFlags = ( newIsAbstract ) ? IS_ABSTRACT_EFLAG : ~IS_ABSTRACT_EFLAG;

The rule has been modified to look for simpler cases.  For example:

if( x ) {
  return a;
} else {
  return b;
}

More complex cases are now ignored

